element.name: You See Eye by AbbeyAckbar, Traditional Cache (1/1)
element.description: This cache is hidden in Howth, on a path less travelled by the usual throng of people that descend there to enjoy a nice walk on the piers most weekends.
element.long-description: This location is a far less frequented part of Howth, as not everybody knows the path is there. The cache is a short walk away from the carpark near the west pier (the working side of the harbour with all the shops & restaurants) Enjoy the view on your walk to the cache and when the tide is out, see if you can spot the Nessie-like shipwreck! or is it Scotland's Loch Ness Monster - on vacation? Please log any Nessie sightings and upload photographic evidence :) Initial Cache Contents: Log, pencil, €2 FTF Prize & 1c(for luck)

ul.li:
2010-05-09T19:00:00Z : Found it by Suburban cowboy
The last one on todays trip to Howth. We had a couple of minutes left before the DART was leaving so we disided to look for this one as a finale. Logged with my muggle sister. And, as the tide was out we even spoted Nessie. Photo will be uploaded as soon as I get back home... [:)] TFTC Suburban cowboy Sweden

2010-05-09T19:00:00Z : Found it by Toffee Man
Nice walk to this cache from the main parking area. TFTC Toffee Man #335

2010-05-09T19:00:00Z : Found it by Blue Jay 59
Lovely walk, and it was quite quiet compared to the other parts of Howth today. Nice views, could only see Nessie's head over the water [:)] TFTC Blue Jay 59 #336

2010-05-02T19:00:00Z : Found it by daviddotshaw
great location good hiding place left 3 little charms and a tiny pencil

2010-04-23T19:00:00Z : Found it by Turfstack
This cache was well named. It was a tiny little container well hidden.
